we first initiate a directory as a repository.
so on the directory that we want to git get track
we write:

git init
it's create ".git" directory on our project

note: ".git" directory is a hidden file.
      so we can see it by:
      ****
          "ls -a" (a stand for all)
      ****
      we can open it by:
      open .git


note: all history data, branches,...
      will store in .git folder
      so if we delete this folder we will lose all the data.
      it's just git detail implementation we don't need it
      that's because why it's hidden
